OL,6,FBirmingham Magistrates Court was told
OL,7,Fhow Mr Pugh and his colleagues began
OL,8,Fworking on a pylon known as Tower AE11
OL,9,Fin preparation for its demolition.
OL,11,FThey were unaware there had been
OL,12,Fprevious work to loosen the bolts on
OL,13,Fthe tower, known as "bolt cracking",
OL,14,Fundertaken by another team of linesmen.
OL,16,FThe court heard that this work had not
OL,17,Fbeen risk assessed and there were no
OL,18,Fsystems in place to effectively record
OL,19,Fand communicate what they had actually
OL,20,Fdone.
