OL,4,Cman paralysed after 30ft fall at work
OL,6,FHe spent six months in hospital and
OL,7,Fhas been left unable to work as a
OL,8,Fresult of his extensive injuries.
OL,10,FAn investigation by the Health and
OL,11,FSafety Executive (HSE) found that Wood
OL,12,FTransmission and Distribution Limited
OL,13,Ffailed to ensure that the work at
OL,14,Fheight was properly planned,
OL,15,Fappropriately supervised, and carried
OL,16,Fout in a manner that was, so far as
OL,17,Fwas reasonably practicable, safe.
