OL,3,CCompany fined #240,000 after fall left
OL,4,Cman paralysed after 30ft fall at work
OL,6,FThe company had not considered the
OL,7,Fwork at height hierarchy as part of
OL,8,Fits planning and had not assessed the
OL,9,Frisks associated with bolt cracking.
OL,11,FIt had also not adequately resourced
OL,12,Fthe task in line with its own safety
OL,13,Fdocumentation, and had failed to put
OL,14,Fin place a process for transferring
OL,15,Fwork between teams and ensuring safety
OL,16,Fcritical information was recorded and
OL,17,Fcommunicated effectively.
