OL,3,CCompany fined #240,000 after fall left
OL,4,Cman paralysed after 30ft fall at work
OL,6,F"Proper assessment of the risks and
OL,7,Fconsideration of work methods,
OL,8,Fadequate staffing, and clear
OL,9,Fprocedures for transferring towers
OL,10,Fbetween teams could have enabled this
OL,11,Fwork to go ahead without incident.
OL,13,F"Instead, because of the company's
OL,14,Fshortcomings, a worker has sadly and
OL,15,Funnecessarily been left paralysed.
OL,17,F"Companies should be aware that HSE
OL,18,Fwill not hesitate to take appropriate
OL,19,Fenforcement action against those that
OL,20,Ffall below the required standards."
